summary: This document appears to be a forensic analysis report from December 5, 2021, detailing user login activity on a computer system, specifically noting a high number of logins (390) for an account named 'ghislaine'. It is subject to a protective order.

persons.name: Ghislaine
persons.context: Appears as a user account on a machine with 390 logins documented in a forensic analysis.

events.title: Forensic Analysis of Computer Logins
events.description: A forensic check of a computer's SAM file and user accounts was conducted, revealing login counts for guest, administrator, and a user named 'ghislaine'.

keyFacts: A forensic analysis on December 5, 2021, examined user login data from a computer system.
The analysis found 390 logins for a user account named 'ghislaine'.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
The analysis also noted approximately 30 logins for an administrator account and zero for a guest account on the system.
